<br>
The first text box &quot;Calendar Text&quot; is for bare minimum information.  This is what shows up on the main page of the calendar.  For the love of God ... please don't type a personal diary here ... as it will stretch the cells vertically - and since HTML is symetrical - you will change the table structure of the whole calendar and make it look sloppy and distorted.<br>
<br>
The &quot;Pop Up Text&quot; textbox is where you can write the first chapter of your love life on Lanys, as well as all the many details about your raid or strike that is planned.  That is what it is there for ... 'Additional Information'.<br>
<br>
So a common entry would look like this:<br>
<br>
5:00pm PoF:  Dark Whispers - Istrahd Leads<br>
<br>
... then in the pop up window:<br>
<br>
Sign up on DW raid board.  Min. level is 46.  Only taking 5 of each class ... first come first serve basis ... so hurry on over if you wanna go.  Make sure to bring your resist gear ... and for those without diamond and BD gear - bring primarily your cold gear just in case Terror is up.  Be at the portal no later than 5pm ... as that is the planned insert time.  Any questions ... ask Leolan ... cause I don't have time for tells.<br>
<br>
...<br>
<br>
That should help out on the size of the cells and keep the calendar looking professional and easy to read.<br>
<br>
One last note - for the love of GOD ... please use colors for text and background that go together ... I just had to fix a blue on blue not too long ago ... and a dark blue with dark green text that could not be read.<br>
<br>
